Either Doug can
remember them all,

01:24:11.775 --> 01:24:13.650
because we're going to
take them all at once,

01:24:13.650 --> 01:24:15.700
or I can jot down what they ask.

01:24:15.700 --> 01:24:17.170
But let's start
over here, please.

01:24:17.170 --> 01:24:17.733
Brief.

01:24:17.733 --> 01:24:20.400
AUDIENCE: First of all, I wanted
say that I've been watching you

01:24:20.400 --> 01:24:22.680
on CNN for years,
and I can't believe

01:24:22.680 --> 01:24:24.735
I'm in the same room with you.

01:24:24.735 --> 01:24:27.160
So it's wonderful.

01:24:27.160 --> 01:24:30.660
My quick question is, I wasn't
born before the moon landing.

01:24:30.660 --> 01:24:35.220
So I mean, but I certainly
know the global and historical

01:24:35.220 --> 01:24:36.480
importance of that.

01:24:36.480 --> 01:24:39.720
But recently China
has landed a craft

01:24:39.720 --> 01:24:42.240
on the dark side of
the moon, and SpaceX

01:24:42.240 --> 01:24:44.340
is talking about going to Mars.

01:24:44.340 --> 01:24:47.430
So I wanted to
basically hear your view

01:24:47.430 --> 01:24:50.773
on the future of space
exploration in our country.

01:24:50.773 --> 01:24:51.690
FREDERIK LOGEVALL: OK.

01:24:51.690 --> 01:24:52.200
Hold that one.

01:24:52.200 --> 01:24:52.700
Yes, sir.

01:24:52.700 --> 01:24:54.492
AUDIENCE: On the question
of an earth shot,

01:24:54.492 --> 01:24:59.650
there are a number of nominees--
climate change, infrastructure,

01:24:59.650 --> 01:25:00.900
health care.

01:25:00.900 --> 01:25:03.450
Is there any that
among those three

01:25:03.450 --> 01:25:07.940
or any other possible
earth shots which

01:25:07.940 --> 01:25:10.910
one would have the best
chance of developing

01:25:10.910 --> 01:25:13.495
a sense of national purpose
that would be bipartisan?

01:25:13.495 --> 01:25:14.870
FREDERIK LOGEVALL:
OK, excellent.

01:25:14.870 --> 01:25:15.843
Yes?

01:25:15.843 --> 01:25:17.510
AUDIENCE: I worked
on the Apollo program

01:25:17.510 --> 01:25:19.820
at MIT under Dr. Draper.

01:25:19.820 --> 01:25:20.632
And I was there.

01:25:20.632 --> 01:25:21.840
FREDERIK LOGEVALL: Wonderful.

